{
  "$comment": "Closed schema for one ingress information-cycle evidence bundle (GH #269 rounds 3-4). Structural layer only; scripts/validate_information_cycle_bundle.py enforces the cross-field contract: the exact 20-stage ledger, the stage-RECORD chain (stage_record_digest over the canonical record minus stage_record_digest and previous_stage_record; every stage links to the immediately preceding record, unproven/failed included), the separate transformation-OUTPUT dependency chain (depends_on_outputs may cite only output-producing stages or explicitly missing prerequisites), implementation provenance (reviewed_commit must be an ancestor containing every component blob; current bytes must still match), the raw-sample allowlist (digest+category only, stage-scoped), and held-vs-required evidence classes (unproven holds none and declares required_evidence_class; the bundle class equals the strongest actually held class). bundle_id digest domain: canonical content excluding bundle_id, started_at, completed_at. Artifact digests are sha256 over LF-normalized bytes.",
  "type": "object",
  "additionalProperties": false,
  "required": [
    "schema_version",
    "bundle_id",
    "run_id",
    "route",
    "evidence_class",
    "integrations",
    "contract",
    "started_at",
    "completed_at",
    "stages",
    "unproven_downstream",
    "implementation_provenance"
  ],
  "properties": {
